+# Planner Portfolio - exact-ns-no-near-closed-tao-circuit / run-001
+
+## Preserved Context
+
+- Tao's averaged-NS mechanism has already been narrowed to a five-mode delayed-threshold circuit with one tiny but decisive trigger variable `X3,n`.
+- The inherited live discrepancy is not generic pressure rhetoric. It is exact-NS circuit non-isolability: exact Navier-Stokes supplies one rigid Leray-projected quadratic law plus full triad summation, while Tao's circuit needs a near-isolated hierarchy of five channels.
+- Prior work already isolated the three load-bearing exact-NS pressures on the idea: coefficient rigidity, unavoidable spectator couplings, and exact projection/reality bookkeeping.
+- Prior work did not yet produce a theorem object, leakage lower bound, or counterexample. This run must do that rather than restating "NS is more entangled."
+- The planner note in the mission requires both a no-circuit direction and an adversarial near-circuit construction direction. This portfolio includes both.
+
+## Portfolio Summary
+
+### Chain 01 - Minimal Helical Coefficient-Rigidity Theorem
+
+Central premise: the smallest exact helical packet capable of mimicking Tao's pump / seed / amplifier / rotor logic already fails because the required sign and magnitude hierarchy cannot be realized by one geometry-locked family of triad coefficients.
+
+### Chain 02 - Spectator-Leakage Lower-Bound Ledger
+
+Central premise: even if some desired channels can be matched, exact Fourier/helical closure plus mirror-mode bookkeeping forces enough extra interactions that any honest Tao-like subsystem leaks a quantifiable amount of activity outside the five target roles.
+
+### Chain 03 - Adversarial Near-Circuit Construction Search
+
+Central premise: the obstruction might be false. The fastest honest kill is to search directly for the best exact NS or helical packet that approximates Tao's logic and see whether it survives exact coupling accounting.
+
+### Chain 04 - Definition-Stability Audit for "Near-Closed Tao Circuit"
+
+Central premise: the whole mission may fail at the object-definition level. If every reasonable definition of near-closure is unstable under phase choice, packetization, scaling, or conjugate completion, the right result is a sharp definitional kill rather than a fake theorem program.
+
+## Major Differences Between Chains
+
+- Chain 01 is algebraic and theorem-facing. It targets incompatible coefficient ratios and sign patterns inside a minimal exact helical model.
+- Chain 02 is closure- and leakage-facing. It assumes desired channels may exist but asks whether forced spectators can be bounded below.
+- Chain 03 is adversarial and constructive. It tries to kill the firewall idea by building the strongest exact near-circuit it can find.
+- Chain 04 is meta-definitional. It tests whether the theorem object itself can be made stable enough to support Chains 01-03.
+
+## Portfolio Discipline
+
+- Every chain must freeze one exact target object before optimism begins: either a minimal helical packet, a leakage functional, a concrete search family, or a formal definition family.
+- Every chain must preserve the inherited negative results: no generic pressure route, no LP cleanup, no Beltrami rhetoric, and no drift back to broad regularity arguments.
+- Every chain must produce a bounded final object: proposition candidate, lower-bound ledger, counterexample candidate, or definition-level obstruction memo.
+- Useful negative results are first-class outputs. This mission does not require a positive obstruction if the best earned conclusion is that the definition or the obstruction idea collapses.
+
+## Suggested Priority
+
+- First priority: Chain 04, because a stable definition is prerequisite for any later theorem or counterexample claim.
+- Second priority: Chain 01, because coefficient rigidity is the cleanest exact mechanism-level theorem target.
+- Third priority: Chain 02, because leakage is the most natural quantitative fallback if pure rigidity does not close.
+- Fourth priority: Chain 03, because it is the essential adversarial check and the cleanest way to kill the firewall idea if the obstruction fails.

